-- McNamara Joins BMO Capital and Scotia Hires Malhotra, Vlaad Says
-- B y   D o u g   A l e x a n d e r
-- 2013-11-22T19:00:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-11-22/mcnamara-joins-bmo-capital-and-scotia-hires-malhotra-vlaad-says.html
Bank of Montreal (BMO) ’s BMO Capital
Markets hired Dan McNamara from Calamos Asset Management to head
its U.S. financial institutions group, according to Vlaad & Co.,
a Toronto-based financial services recruiting firm.  Other moves noted in the “Bill’s Buzz” weekly  newsletter 
include:2  * Analyst Sumit Malhotra joined Bank of  Nova Scotia  to cover
financial services from Macquarie Group Ltd.  * Tashi Dorji joined Haywood Securities Inc. to cover oil and
gas from Toronto-Dominion Bank.  * Cormark Securities Ltd. hired Meny Grauman as a financial
services analyst from Canadian Imperial Bank of Commerce, where
he was a senior equity research associate.  * Ben Jekic joined Industrial Alliance Securities as an analyst
covering industrial products and special situations. He was
previously a consultant at BVB Consulting Inc. and a hardware
analyst at Desjardins Securities.  * Romain Marguet joined JC Clark Ltd. as a director of business
development. He previously worked for a boutique private equity
firm in Geneva.  * Jeffrey Mandell joined Fuller Landau LLP as a managing
director in its corporate finance and mergers and acquisitions
team. He was previously manager of corporate finance at Cranson
Capital Solutions Inc.  To contact the reporter on this story:
